# UPDATE 
Cortex.t 2.5.0 will be pushed to main in the next 15-30 mins. **Please EVERYONE update as soon as possible. **

## CHANGELOG:

Extensive rewrite of the entire codebase

### Validator

#### Wandb
- changed to a new project (last one had over 40k runs and 3 TB of storage used)
- added an encrypted signature to the wandb run that can only be encrypted by your specific hotkey in that way.
- excluded score logging to decrease storage requirements

#### Structure
- refactored the script into validator classes for each modality
- New modality alert! Embeddings validator coming very soon

#### Main loop
- improve the speed of uid active checking while simultaneously decreasing the error rate and allowing for slower machines
- added async awaiting of metagraph syncing and other processes to improve overall efficiency
- changed iterations until set weights from 3 to 10 with this faster processing
- changed the ratio at which we process the modalities from 1:1 text:image to 3:1 text:image
- added a min-max normalization for better logging display of weights

#### Text modality
- changed timeout to 36 seconds to avoid answers being cut off from miners
- changed logging to include the newlines from the answers
- changed the strategy of synthetic data generation to be instruct and knowledge tasks for efficiently extracting the essence of gpt4
- added over 30 broad range default categorical themes for instruct tasks
- added a method for uniformly sampling a range of differing complexity and relevance level questions for each category (10k per category)
- added popping from the sampling to not replace previously asked questions
- improved the robustness of the extract list function to minimize exceptions in processing lists

#### Image modality
- changed weight to .33
- added async response handling which vasly improves validator efficiency
- added an element of randomness to validator scoring to increase speed
- added 1000 unique default themes for image generation
- changed the prompting method to elicit new and more creative and diverse prompts
- improved list extraction
 
#### reward.py
- added linearly decaying similarity requirements with openai answer because of non-perfect floating point operations for token selection

#### Protocol.py
- changed the text processing to not split by newline and instead process every token individually
- improved the format of ImageResponse to be consistent with the other classes as pydantic fields

#### other
- added an autoupdate script that checks every 5 minutes for version updates on github. If a version upgrade is found, it git pulls, pip installs, and restarts pm2
- optionally autoupdate, but you can also opt in to receive an automated discord DM in the event of a version upgrade
i- ncreased openai client timeout to avoid errors

### MINERS

We have implemented a sophisticated blacklisting mechanism within the miner, which confers multiple advantages. Previously, the absence of a blacklist function meant that any key could query the system, regardless of its registration status on the network. The introduction of this new feature enhances security and efficiency in several ways.

Primarily, it initiates a dedicated thread that executes a loop every three minutes to monitor all wandb runs associated with our new project. This process involves verifying the hotkey, signature, and version specified in the configuration of each run. By doing so, we ensure that the hotkey is duly registered, the signature accurately decodes the hex (confirming the identity of the wandb run's initiator as the legitimate owner of the validator), and the version corresponds with the most recent release on GitHub. Should any of these criteria not be met, the validator in question will be blacklisted.
This update mandates prompt version updates by validators, which can be facilitated through our auto-update script. The benefits of this requirement include the prevention of malformed requests and the elimination of outdated protocol versions, thereby mitigating potential disruptions. Moreover, it effectively curtails any improper activities.

A particularly noteworthy aspect of this update is the restriction it places on weight copiers, denying them any network bandwidth. As a miner, it is counterproductive to engage with entities that do not contribute to the scoring of responses or to the generation of emissions data. By excluding such entities from utilizing any API services on their validator, we ensure that they are contributing to the collective effort of gathering synthetic data for the training of future models. This approach presents no disadvantages for miners and, in fact, optimizes available bandwidth for interactions with legitimate validators.

## BUGS & FEEDBACK

You can now submit bugs and feedback directly to us with this form: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeeplNpJBIwHV39e3HymauDbPogCia4HO_2tUme_WJJM9mThw/viewform?pli=1

Thank you.
